703
00:55:01,160 --> 00:55:05,300
What do you mean it hurts?
I'm applying it so gently.

704
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:22,400
- All done.
- Ouch!

705
00:55:22,460 --> 00:55:25,000
- You're grateful, right?
- I'm grateful.

706
00:55:33,630 --> 00:55:34,660
It's late, but I wanted
to congratulate you

707
00:55:34,730 --> 00:55:36,200
on coming home from the hospital.

708
00:55:36,500 --> 00:55:38,060
What is it?

709
00:55:44,130 --> 00:55:45,960
It's a necklace.

710
00:55:46,700 --> 00:55:48,230
I'll put it on for you.

711
00:56:19,300 --> 00:56:23,460
Then are we officially
going out now?

712
00:56:25,560 --> 00:56:28,430
Well, it depends on
how you behave...

713
00:56:30,160 --> 00:56:31,400
I will behave.

714
00:56:31,460 --> 00:56:33,700
See what happens
if you're seen with another girl.

715
00:56:33,760 --> 00:56:35,960
It won't happen again.

716
00:56:36,660 --> 00:56:38,730
You're the only one for me.

717
00:56:41,760 --> 00:56:43,630
Get home safe.

718
00:56:44,700 --> 00:56:46,030
See you tomorrow.

719
00:56:46,530 --> 00:56:48,030
Good night.

720
00:56:48,630 --> 00:56:50,360
You have a good night, too.

721
00:57:36,400 --> 00:57:39,400
- What took you so long?
- I told you I'd see friends today.

722
00:57:39,460 --> 00:57:42,030
- Can you be here alone for a bit?
- Sure.

723
00:57:42,100 --> 00:57:44,500
I'm not a little kid. Why ask?

724
00:57:44,560 --> 00:57:47,400
I'm going over to your uncle's.

725
00:57:47,460 --> 00:57:50,430
- Lock up, okay?
- I will.

726
00:57:51,500 --> 00:57:53,760
- Wait, mom.
- Yes?

727
00:57:53,830 --> 00:57:57,330
- Get me ice cream on your way home.
- You got it.

728
00:58:00,660 --> 00:58:03,930
- See you later.
- See you later.

729
00:58:27,960 --> 00:58:30,930
Sir, what are you looking at?

730
00:58:32,060 --> 00:58:34,360
I'm looking at the record
of the cars Ju has had.

731
00:58:34,430 --> 00:58:37,430
A white car was seen
at the hit-and-run scene, right?

732
00:58:37,500 --> 00:58:39,630
Yes, it was a white sedan.

733
00:58:39,700 --> 00:58:42,630
No other information was available.

734
00:58:43,930 --> 00:58:47,830
Ju drove a white car five years ago.

735
00:58:47,900 --> 00:58:50,130
- He did?
- On August 25th, 2011

736
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:52,600
- he scrapped it.
- Hold on.

737
00:58:52,660 --> 00:58:57,900
- That's 2 days after the accident.
- That's right.

738
00:58:58,660 --> 00:59:01,160
What interesting timing…

739
00:59:16,130 --> 00:59:20,060
(Kim Hyun-ji)

740
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:06,960
Bong-pal.

741
01:00:31,230 --> 01:00:33,630
Hyun-ji, what's wrong?
What happened?

742
01:00:33,700 --> 01:00:35,600
Bong-pal.

743
01:00:37,900 --> 01:00:39,800
What should I do now?

744
01:00:42,330 --> 01:00:45,630
What I saw at the hospital
wasn't a one-time thing…

745
01:00:48,300 --> 01:00:50,460
I can see ghosts.

746
01:01:04,730 --> 01:01:06,500
She's human now.

747
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:08,500
She deserves to have a normal life.

748
01:01:08,560 --> 01:01:12,430
You don't know how it will affect
her if she finds out the truth.

749
01:01:12,500 --> 01:01:16,160
- Hyun-ji.
- What should I do now?

750
01:01:24,460 --> 01:01:26,330
Don't worry.

751
01:01:28,660 --> 01:01:32,330
No matter what happens

752
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:34,330
I will protect you.

753
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:34,460
(Bring it on, Ghost)

754
01:02:34,660 --> 01:02:37,000
Now Hyun-ji can see ghosts.

755
01:02:37,060 --> 01:02:39,160
If a ghost attacks you this way...

756
01:02:39,730 --> 01:02:41,800
Let's practice
as if it's a real situation.

757
01:02:42,400 --> 01:02:44,560
How did you get to know Bong-pal?

758
01:02:44,630 --> 01:02:47,160
- It was like fate.
- I miss you.

759
01:02:47,230 --> 01:02:49,760
I don't want her to
live like me so please, help.

760
01:02:49,830 --> 01:02:53,460
He's not after Bong-pal next, is he?

761
01:02:53,530 --> 01:02:54,260
What's wrong?

762
01:02:54,330 --> 01:02:56,460
I thought I got my memory
back from the accident.

763
01:02:56,530 --> 01:02:59,130
- Is he Park Ji-hoon?
- You go alone.

764
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:00,300
Bong-pal!

765
01:03:00,360 --> 01:03:02,600
- Where are we going?
- It's kind of far from here.

